  "button3Text": {
    "id": "button3Text",
    "x": 746,
    "y": 600,
    "width": 500,
    "z": 9732,
    "movable": false,
    "text": "The cards, cubes, and marbles all use RESET for the `parent` property. The cards have the reset property on the `cardDefaults` and the Ace has an additional reset directly on it. The cards and cubes are moved in an order not controllable by the game designer. Use a sort, shuffle or whatever else is appropriate. Order of the properties in the reset property matters. For example, the marbles are being parented to the seat in a particular location. But the yellow marble has its parent set after the x/y are set, so it is not in the location you might expect. "
  },
